cd to the directory where you have your "Dockerfile"

To Build Dcoker Image:
   docker build -t springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE . 

To check docker images:
    docker images  

To run a docker image:
     docker run -p 8080:8080 springboot-docker-demo 
                   or
     docker run -p 8081:8080 springboot-docker-demo 
     Note: Here 8081 is the host port and 8080 is the container port

To check the docker containers running:
    docker ps 

To start a docker container in a detached mode:
     docker run -p 8081:8080 -d springboot-docker-demo

To see the logs on the docker container running in detached mode:
     docker logs -f 7d5f    (Note: Here 7d5f are the first four characters of the docker container running)

To stop the docker container running in detached mode:
     docker stop 7d5f 

Docker login:
     docker login  

To link a docker image with a repository on docker hub:
      docker tag springboot-docker-demo mehdavi/springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE
      docker push mehdavi/springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE 
      docker pull mehdavi/springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE   
      docker run -p 8080:8080 mehdavi/springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE 